SIMPLE: constrictor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Constrictor
<hw>Con*strict"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
which constricts, draws together, or contracts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A muscle which contracts or
closes an orifice, or which compresses an organ; a sphincter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A serpent that kills its prey by
inclosing and crushing it with its folds; <as>as, the boa
<ex>constrictor</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Constringe</ent>⟦br⟧
